title: Arsonist torches cars in West Seattle
text:
People in West Seattle want to know who tried to blow up their cars Sunday.
The fires were set under the gas tanks of the cars along Sylvan Heights Drive about 4:40 a.m.
In both cases, the fires were started in a container placed under the gas tanks.
KIRO 7 spoke with Egan Fowler, who woke up early yesterday to his car alarm going off.
He saw his Subaru, and the neighbor's car right next to it, on fire.
“That fire was right under the gas tank, so they knew what they were doing,” said Fowler. “My car had a probably six feet high - there was a flame off the back.”
No one was hurt and the car owners were able to put out the fires as firefighters arrived.
Anyone who has any information about the fires is asked to call 911.
